speech.p: Does the Prime Minister agree with me and the 10,800 of my constituents who have signed petitions that the building of a gasification plant in Washington would be terrible for the people of Sunderland due to public health and air quality concerns, and that it would be a blot on the landscape of Sunderland? Now that he is a frequent visitor to Sunderland, I am sure he shares my concerns on this matter. Will he therefore support me and my constituents who oppose the building of this plant?
